
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to concatenate strings to construct a SQL query dynamically. It uses [set-value] to update the [.sql] node by appending an "order by" clause and a "limit" clause to an existing SQL query. The [strings.concat] slot is used to concatenate the current SQL query with additional strings, including the "order by" and "limit" clauses. The [get-value] slot retrieves the current SQL query and the limit value from the [.arguments] node to complete the SQL statement. 
 * 
 * 1. [set-value] - Updates the value of the [.sql] node.
 * 2. [strings.concat] - Concatenates strings to form a SQL query.
 * 3. [get-value] - Retrieves the existing SQL query.
 * 4. [.] - Static string to append to the SQL query.
 * 5. [get-value] - Retrieves the limit value from the [.arguments] node.
 */
set-value:x:@.sql
   strings.concat:x:@.sql
      get-value:x:@.sql
      .:" order by keyword_count desc, keyword_density desc limit "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/limit
